items.author: Candice C. Dejournett

items.title: 4.0 out of 5 stars REALLY nice, 2 notes: runs a little too oversized & neckline is a bit tight
items.body: This sweater is incredible and almost perfect. The material is super soft and it’s pretty heavyweight, it will keep you warm on a fairly cold day. As others have noted it’s a bit more oversized than you would expect. I am 5’7” 165 lbs ordered my regular size L, and I like the way it looks but I would note that the arms are so long that the tips of my fingernails just barely poke out when standing with my arms down, and the arms are also extra baggy. The sweater is a little long on me, it’s more like tunic length. I think the way it fits would make it perfect for pairing with leggings. So it does run a little extra oversized but I don’t mind it personally af all. The other thing I would note is mostly for anyone who has sensory issues or for any reason struggles with necklines that are a bit too close to the neck, that this runs tighter / closer to the neck than most crew neck sweaters. It feels more like a turtleneck as far as the feeling at the neck and at first I was bummed as I wasn’t gonna be able to wear it. However it’s a rather stretchy material so I manually stretched the neckline for about a minute and put it back on and it helped a lot, although it’s still a little tighter than I prefer, I can handle it now. But if you are able to wear things like turtlenecks than this won’t be an issue for you at all, unless you are sensitive to clothes around your neck it otherwise is unlikely to be noticeable. I just wanted to mention this for anyone else that might have neckline sensitivities like I have. They’re the only two issues I had with an otherwise perfect sweater! Since I don’t mind it running a little extra oversize at all and I was able to fix the neck line issue so that it’s tolerable for me, I really don’t have any problems with this sweater at all. In fact, it is one of my absolute favorites for the rare cold days where I live. But if you don’t have neckline sensitivities and would prefer a more traditionally oversize fit, you may want to consider ordering this one size down from your normal sweater size. But the fabric, material, style, color etc are all perfect and match the seller’s photos. Hope this helps! Read more
items.author: Mother of LEGOs

items.title: 5.0 out of 5 stars OVERSIZED!
items.body: I bought this sweater for me and even after washing found it way too big. In a sweater I normally wear XL to allow for other garments to be worn under. This sweater swalloed me up! My husband is 6'4" and so I had him try it on. It fits perfect! While advertised for women, it's not particularly girly and so he will wear it. In this respect, I'd call it uni-sex. The sweater is really very nice. The weave is even and consitent. The seams are well sewn and tight. The edging is nice. Against bare skin it's a little scratchy - kind of like wool but less so. There is a band running down the back giving it a nice touch. Though not being used as intended, this nice sweater, I predict, will see many a cold mornings in the near future! Read more
items.author: BellOnWheels

items.title: 4.0 out of 5 stars Label should list the fiber content, nice oversized comfortable feel and look
items.body: A little too big and sloppy for my taste, but that's the style now. I love the warm color--light tan, slightly more brown than khaki or beige. Feels like wool, but isn't (even a little bit of wool makes me itch.) I'd give it a higher rating if it listed the fiber content. Although it says handwash, it machine-washes up fine on cold & delicate, and laying out flat it dries without wrinkles. Otherwise, it seems to wrinkle pretty easily if you don't fold it up carefully. Good for weekends, feeling under the weather, or extra warmth over slimmer sweaters. Read more
items.author: Customer

items.title: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good Quality Oversized Sweater
items.body: "Okay, I'm obsessed with this sweater! It's literally the coziest thing I've ever put on. The oversized fit is perfection - it's like a big hug in sweater form The knit is super soft and doesn't pill easily, which is a huge plus. I've worn it a bunch already and it still looks like new. It's perfect for lazy days, running errands, or layering under a jacket. It is great for tucking into jeans or leggings. Honestly, this sweater is a wardrobe essential. Would totally recommend! Read more
items.author: gregory j.

items.title: 4.0 out of 5 stars Cozy and Versatile Sweater for Any Occasion
items.body: This oversized crewneck sweater has turned into one of those pieces I keep reaching for without thinking about it. The fabric feels really soft and cozy, and it does a good job of keeping warmth in on colder days. I’ve washed it a few times now and it’s held its shape well, which isn’t always the case with softer knits. The relaxed fit works nicely on its own and leaves enough room to layer underneath. It looks just as good with jeans as it does with leggings, so it’s easy to throw on for different situations. I also like the ribbed cuffs and hem since they add a little structure without feeling tight. Overall, it’s comfortable, easy to wear, and fits right into everyday rotation. Read more
items.author: Product Feedback

items.title: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very nice ladies sweater
items.body: My mother and I wet Christmas shopping and I let her wear this. She really likes it. The fabric is very nice to the touch. The weight lets you know you have on a sweater, but not so heavy that it feels like it is dragging you down. For my mother, this is a perfect fit and really seems to be a great value for the money. Read more
items.author: 43rpetty

items.title: 3.0 out of 5 stars Oh yes, very very oversized! Soft sweater too!
items.body: Definitely oversized, to the point where I should really have a small. I ordered the medium. The sleeves are toooo long, I have to fold the cuffs up to fit properly. The fabric is very soft though and the sweater itself seems to be very well made. My husband tried it on and he loves it. haha. So I guess it will be his. Pretty good quality for the price! Read more

short_description:
Womens Maxi Dress Long Sleeve is made for a polished look that still feels comfortable to wear. It is designed to sit cleanly on the body with a flattering shape that works for day plans and dressier moments without feeling overdone.

The fit focuses on balance rather than extremes, so you can move naturally while still getting a defined silhouette. Choose your usual size for a closer look, or size up if you prefer a little more ease through the waist and hips.

Styling is simple: keep accessories minimal for a clean finish, or add a jacket and statement shoes when you want a sharper outfit. This piece photographs well thanks to smooth lines and a structured feel that stays put once you have it adjusted.

With the right fit and simple styling, this item becomes an easy go-to when you want something that looks intentional without requiring extra effort.

This piece transitions well from daytime plans to evening events with a quick change of shoes and a small bag or clutch.

long_description:
Womens Maxi Dress Long Sleeve is a versatile piece you can reach for when you want a put-together look that still feels comfortable. The goal is simple: a silhouette that reads polished, photographs well, and stays wearable for a full day or a long night.

Fit and sizing Fit is where most outfits win or lose. This design aims for a balanced shape with a defined line through the torso, a clean waist, and a smooth finish through the hips and legs. If you prefer a more relaxed feel, size up; if you like a closer fit, stay true to size. Sizes may include: One Size.

Fabric and comfort Comfort is not just about softness. It is also about movement and how the fabric behaves as you walk, sit, and stand. A fabric blend with a bit of give helps it keep its shape while still feeling wearable.

Highlights A clean neckline and a refined silhouette for an elevated look. Designed to layer easily with jackets, wraps, or sweaters. Works well with both minimal accessories and statement pieces.

How to style Styling ideas: keep it minimal with neutral shoes and one standout accessory. For a relaxed daytime look, add a denim jacket or cardigan. For events, switch to a bolder shoe and a small clutch for a sharper finish.

Color notes Available colors may include: Khaki, White, Beige, Black, Grey. If a shade is sold out, check back as availability can change.

Care Care guidance matters if you want it to keep its shape and finish. Follow the label first.
